{
  "name": "clayround",
  "description": "A sweet ocarina singing round clay-flute melodies over a warm hill at dusk-bright. Round hollow ocarina tones, pure and soft-edged with a warm woody breath, answer a brighter clay-whistle counter-line over a low clay-jug floor. A warm low-ocarina holds the sweet hollow middle; high whistle-pings and tiny breath-flick glints sparkle on top; a soft layered-ocarina bloom and a breathy three-whistle cloud open lush over a gentle clay-breath texture, with a bright little birdlike chirp for an accent. A major pentatonic at A=432, additive and clean, room reverb, folk-bright and tender — every register covered, never thin, never dreary.",
